!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

graceful /ˈɡreɪsfʊl/

1. ADJ Someone or something that is graceful moves in a smooth and controlled way that is attractive to watch. 优雅的 

例： His movements were so graceful they seemed effortless. 他的动作如此优雅，看似非常从容自如。 

2. gracefully ADV 优雅地 [ADV with v] 

例： She stepped gracefully onto the stage. 她步态优雅地走上舞台。 

3. ADJ Something that is graceful is attractive because it has a pleasing shape or style. 优美的 

例： His handwriting, from earliest young manhood, was flowing and graceful. 从他刚刚成年时起，他的书法就流畅而优美。 

4. gracefully ADV 优美地 [ADV adj/-ed] 

例： She loved the gracefully high ceiling, with its white-painted cornice. 她喜欢那雅致的、檐口被漆成白色的高高的天花板。

</div>

